table of contents
capital employed
capital employed is a measure of net investment. when viewed
from the perspective of how the capital is used by the businesses, it includes exxonmobils net share of property, plant and equipment and other assets less liabilities, excluding both short-term and long-term debt. when viewed from the
perspective of the sources of capital employed for the total corporation, it includes exxonmobils share of total debt and shareholders equity. both of these views include exxonmobils share of amounts applicable to equity companies,
which we believe should be included to provide a more comprehensive measure of capital employed.
